response.overview: Piazza Duomo, the heart of Milan, is transformed into a huge concert hall again. The La Scala Philharmonic Orchestra conducted by Ricardo Shay performs Antonin Dvořák's Symphony No. 9 in e minor and a tribute to Nino Rota, one of the most original and genius Italian composers of the 20th century, on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of his death. to play Dvořák's 'Bohemian' symphony is one of the world's most loved repertoires with a thrilling rhythm inspired by American folk music. The OST is the fruit of a long collaboration between directors Federico Fellini and Nino Rota, two world-renowned masters born in Italy.
response.title: Duomo concert in Milan
